nessus-libraries (1.2.5-2) unstable; urgency=low

  * libnessus-dev's includes.h includes openssl headers, so it has to
    depend on libssl-dev, thanks to James Troup for noticing, closes: #159326.
    Perhaps the OpenSSL dependency should be removed from the header file
    instead, but the upstream likes it better this way.
  * Reworked the remaining libpcap-nessus exclusion patches.

 -- Josip Rodin <jrodin@jagor.srce.hr>  Mon,  2 Sep 2002 21:57:16 +0200

nessus-libraries (1.2.5-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream version.
  * This version no longer uses MAXHOSTNAMELEN in the place the old patch
    was fixing. It uses it in another location, but there it defines a
    default if the constant is not available. If this fixed default is
    still a problem for the Hurd (it shouldn't be, but what do I know),
    please send in another patch, closes: #106386.
  * ACKing NMU bug, closes: #156200.
  * Removed the pretty much pointless libc6-dev dependency from the -dev
    package.

