nessus-libraries (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream version.
  * Package names changed, since lib{hosts_gatherer,nessus} has 1 in the
    SONAME. Additionally, I renamed libnessus1-dev to just libnessus-dev,
    since there's not going to be a need for several -dev packages, ever.
  * Added Conflicts: libnessus0-dev to libnessus-dev, and Conflicts:
    libnessus0 to libnessus1, because of duplicate headers and the same
    libpeks library.
  * Had to use manually written shlibs file, because dh_makeshlibs generated
    the entry for libpeks.so.0.8 wrong. :/
  * Used the new upstream scheme for specifying gmp and zlib in libpeks/*,
    plus a few new fixes of my own.

 -- Josip Rodin <jrodin@jagor.srce.hr>  Sun, 14 May 2000 13:44:28 +0200

