nessus-libraries (0.98.4-3) unstable; urgency=low

  * Not only link libpeks* with dynamic libgmp2, but also don't *build*
    the included gmp2... thanks to gorgo again, for noticing. Closes: #49407.
  * After upstream confirmed it, removed all references to libpcap-nessus,
    and point to system libpcap instead.
  * Do 'cd libpeks/doc && make install' in debian/rules, to install a
    more complete set of libpeks documentation.
  * Standards-Version: 3.1.0.

 -- Josip Rodin <jrodin@jagor.srce.hr>  Mon,  8 Nov 1999 14:39:52 +0100

